-- France, Portugal, Greece, Croatia Advance to Soccer World Cup
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2013-11-19T23:35:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-19/france-portugal-greece-croatia-advance-to-soccer-world-cup.html
France , Portugal and Croatia won to
advance to the World Cup, while Greece booked a place at
soccer’s showpiece with a 1-1 draw in Romania.  Cristiano Ronaldo scored three second-half goals as
Portugal won 3-2 in Sweden for a 4-2 victory over the two-game
playoff series. Zlatan Ibrahimovic got both Sweden’s goals.  France, which won the tournament as host in 1998, beat
Ukraine 3-0 to advance after losing the first game 2-0 in Kiev.  After a 0-0 draw in the first game, Croatia beat the
visiting Iceland 2-0 to go through, while Greece earned its
place with a 4-2 series total.  The World Cup is scheduled from June 12 to July 13 in
 Brazil .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  